content: Neat concept, but very unintuitive and the UI is terrible. The graphics  don't seem to fit on my display (first gen Pixel), with buttons and text  cutting off. Also, many things don't scroll far enough. I spent about for  five minutes with the game, couldn't really figure anything out to the  point where I was enjoying myself, and uninstalled it. Sure to it being so  unintuitive, there really needs to be a tutorial it something. I'm  generally not a big fan of games holding your hand too much but in this  case I would want just that, at least for a little bit.  UPDATE 3/28/19:  The dev responded to my comment any positive communication is worth an extra star. It still doesn't fill my screen (I now have an S9+), but at least I can see. The controls are still shaky, and it's hard to get started, but once you figure out the controls it's not bad. There are a lot of things that don't work, though, such as the automatic selling feature that the game tells you about. The button to turn it on straight up doesn't do anything. Also, some actions take too long to be fun, and you can't do anything but watch it do nothing. Cracking a WPA2 network literally took 40 minutes of real time.

You shouldn't charge for something that's completely undeveloped, and you shouldn't force people to read the reviews to find out that it's a demo - I'd be getting a refund if I hadn't gotten this free during a sale. The new content is fun, but still sparse, and my original comment remains - this is still a demo, and the description should reflect that.
